# Cloudflare Pages response headers for the WarrantOS browser verifier.
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# The page is a single static file with no external requests: it verifies
# a dropped .warrant bundle entirely client-side (see web/README.md). The
# CSP below mirrors the <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"> already
# inlined in index.html (default-src 'none'; script-src 'unsafe-inline';
# style-src 'unsafe-inline'; img-src data:) so the two policies agree, plus
# base-uri, form-action and frame-ancestors, which only take effect as an
# HTTP header and cannot be set via a <meta> tag.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  X-Frame-Options: DENY

/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'none'; script-src 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'unsafe-inline'; img-src data:; base-uri 'none'; form-action 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'
